===Round 2=== Round 2 began August 10 and lasted until November 23, 2014. A total of 16 games were played with 14 players receiving first round byes joining the nine winners from round 1. For the second year in a row multiple major titleholder Akira Watanabe loses in round 2. Also, for the second year in a row, Kōta Kanai beats Toshiaki Kubo in the round 2. Takeshi Fujii had to play two games against Yasumitsu Satō before a winner was determined. The first game between the two ended in [[sennichite]] after 70 moves. A second game with sente-gote reversed was then played with Fujii winning in 121 moves.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Dai Rokujūyonkai NHK Shōgi Terebi Tōnamento Nikaisen Dai Jūkyoku|script-title=ja:第64回NHK将棋テレビトーナメント2回戦第10局|language=ja|trans-title=64th NHK TV Shogi Tournament Round 2 Game 10|airdate= October 12, 2014|last1=Shimizu|first1=Ichiyo (host)|last2=Hirose|first2=Akihito (guest analyst)|network=[[NHK-E]]|series=64th NHK TV Shogi Tournament}}</ref> Hisashi Namekata and Shingo Sawada also needed two games for a winner to be determined. The first game between the two ended in [[Shogi#Winning|impasse]] after 252 moves, and Namekata won the replay with sente-gote reversed in 88 moves. {| class="wikitable" style="width:100%" |- !width="20"|No. !!width="20"|Block !! Sente !! Gote !!width="100"| No. of moves!!width="120"| Date !! Guest Analyst |- | align="center"| 1 || align="center"| A || Akira Watanabe 2 crown ||'''Yūki Sasaki 5d''' || align="center"| 156 || August 10, 2014 ||Nobuyuki Yashiki 9d |- | align="center"| 2 || align="center"| A || '''Kōta Kanai 5d''' || Toshiaki Kubo 9d || align="center"| 95 || August 17, 2014 || Daisuke Suzuki 8d |- | align="center"| 3 || align="center"| B ||'''Nobuyuki Yashiki 9d''' || Takayuki Yamasaki 8d || align="center"| 95 || August 24, 2014 || Kensuke Kitahama 8d |- | align="center"| 4 || align="center"| A ||'''Tadashi Ōishi 6d''' || Akira Inaba 7d || align="center"| 151 || August 31, 2014 || Tetsurō Itodani 6d |- | rows