{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox Olympic event | event = Pairs figure skating | games = 1920 Summer | image = | caption = | venue = [[Palais de Glace d'Anvers]] | date = 26 April | competitors = 16 | nations = 6 | longnames = yes | gold = [[Ludowika Jakobsson]] / [[Walter Jakobsson]] | goldNOC = FIN | silver = [[Alexia Bryn]] / [[Yngvar Bryn]] | silverNOC = NOR | bronze = [[Phyllis Johnson]] / [[Basil Williams (figure skater)|Basil Williams]] | bronzeNOC = GBR | prev = [[Figure skating at the 1908 Summer Olympics – Pairs|1908]] | next = [[Figure skating at the 1924 Winter Olympics – Pairs|1924]] }}
{{Figure skating at the 1920 Summer Olympics}}
The '''[[pair skating]]''' event held as part of the [[figure skating at the 1920 Summer Olympics]]. It was the second appearance of the pair skating event and the sport, which had previously been held in 1908.
Eight pairs from six nations competed. Bronze medalist [[Phyllis Johnson]] had captured the silver medal at the [[1908 Summer Olympics|1908 Olympics]] with a different partner.
