'''Training Centre Petar Miloševski''' ([[Macedonian Cyrillic]]: Тренинг Центар Петар Милошевски) is a football multi-pitch complex in [[Skopje]], [[Republic of Macedonia]]. It is the official training centre of the [[Football Federation of Macedonia]] (FFM). Originally, it was named as ''Training Centre FFM'', but in 2014 it is renamed after the former football national team goalkeeper [[Petar Miloševski]], who died in a car accident earlier that year. 

It is usually the home ground of the Macedonian national youth football teams. The seating capacity of the centre is 2,500 people.

